[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m If an encounter's `current_unit` is not present in `UNIT_CATALOG` (because of a typo, an ADT mapping miss, a unit that was renamed, or a unit that the bed-management team added after the catalog was last updated), the count silently aggregates under that unknown key. `compose_census` then filters with `if u in unit_index`:
